Niger Gets $99 Million Loan From China for Mine, Reuters Says

-- B y   M k h u l u l i   M a n c o t y w a
-- 
2011-04-01T15:35:08Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-01/niger-gets-99-million-loan-from-china-for-mine-reuters-says.html
Niger received a 650 million yuan
($99 million) loan from  China ’s Export-Import Bank to build the
Azelik uranium mine in the country’s north,  Reuters  reported,
citing a government statement.  The loan is repayable over 15 years with a five-year grace
period and an interest rate of 2 percent, the  news agency 
reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mkhululi Mancotywa in Johannesburg at 
